Then again, it's usually the cry babies with half the information that you need to worry about. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I guess I must be missing some information then. Please enlighten me why the following change to manaburn would be bad <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> for wizards</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
<br>
A. make manaburn do damage based on max mana instead of current mana<br>
<br>
B. Add a flag that means manaburn can't hit again for 20 seconds.<br>
<br>
Possible objections:<br>
<br>
1. would nerf manaburn, on which I spent my aaxp points.<br>
No, it would make it more powerful. Instead of always burning at the start of a fight, then modding back to nuke, you can nuke freely and burn on demand, to deal with gaters/rampage etc.<br>
<br>
It would only specifically hurt all-manaburn forces.<br>
<br>
2. manaburn only really affects Kunark dragons, which are trivial<br>
If they are trivial, what is the objection ot this change? <br>
<br>
3. manaburn helps smaller guilds pull off kills and get epics<br>
This still allows one manaburn wizard to make a massive contribution to a raid, and two to make victory almost certain. Any guild that has 3 or more manaburn wizards does not count as small.<br>
<br>
4. manaburning Kunark dragons is like a level 30 wizard nuking Emperor Crush<br>
Most people do this once and leave crushbone to those of the right level. On my server, 80% of recent outdoor Kunark dragons spawns have been taken by all-manaburn groups.<br>
<br>
This is analogous to what used to happen back before Kunark, where a single wizard was almost guaranteed to be able to KS from a group. So wizards and druids, some of them farming for ebay sales, would literally monopolise a particular named spawn, timing the pops, porting in, burning, and moving on to the next one on their list.<br>
<br>
That got changed, by randomising spawn times and making total group damage count towards who gets the kill. Anyone care to argue that that was not a good and needed change?<br>
<br>
5. farming doesn't happen on my server<br>
Then this change won't affect you.<br>
<br>
6. wizards used to be underpowered so now deserve ultimate power<br>
By that logic, if wizards now have ultimate power, they deserve to be nerfed. <br>
The game is the way it is, history doesn't come into it.<br>
<br>
7. we don't sell the loot, we give it away<br>
'How did you get your epic Bob? Slay a dragon?'<br>
'Nah, i just hung out in the right zone until some high levels ganked the dragon and let me take the leavings'<br>
<br>
8. manaburn has a long reuse time<br>
But shorter than spawn times.<br>
<br>
9. getting together all of the manaburn wizards on a server is very difficult<br>
Getting together 20% of the wizards on a server is very easy. Levelling happens, what was rare yesterday is commonplace today and ubiquitous tomorrow.<br>
<br>
9. Verant knew what they were doing when they designed manaburn<br>
<br>
*laughs hysterically*<br>
<br>
10. You are jealous, and you just want to get wizards nerfed.<br>
<br>
No, i just want to hear what you have to say. I like a nice rational discussion, and I would love to hear some new arguments. If they persuade me, I'll use them the next time the subject of manaburn nerfing comes up.<br>
<br>
Seriously, you wizards have shown yourselves to be quite capable of having rational arguments on other areas of game balance, where a power boost for wizards could easily be justified. Is there some reason this particular area is so emotional?<br>
<br>
Soru<br>
